  <h2>How CPC Delivers Education Cleaning</h2>
  <p>
    CPC manages education facility cleaning through compliant workforce practices, infection control protocols applied as standard rather than only during outbreaks, and service schedules designed around school operations from the ground up. Multi-campus portfolio management is supported by centralised reporting and dedicated contract management.
  </p>
  <p>
    CPC's holiday deep clean programs are planned and executed against education calendar cycles with completion documentation provided to facility managers. Outbreak response protocols are pre-planned for common infectious disease scenarios and can be activated without delay when required by school leadership.
  </p>

  <h2>Workforce and Training Model</h2>
  <p>
    CPC operates a vetted workforce model combining directly employed core staff with contractor partners who meet our compliance, training and screening requirements. All workforce deployed with unsupervised student access hold current working with children checks appropriate to the state of service delivery.
  </p>
  <p>
    Infection control training is applied as a standard element of education site inductions. Site-specific training covers chemical management and storage, emergency procedures, and student safeguarding awareness. Supervisors maintain compliance records for all workforce credentials and coordinate renewal before expiry.
  </p>

  <h2>Reporting, Auditing and Evidence of Work</h2>
  <p>CPC provides schools and education portfolios with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Inspection reports and attendance records confirming service delivery</li>
    <li>Compliance documentation for workforce credentials including WWCC records</li>
    <li>Deep clean completion evidence formatted for facility manager acquittal</li>
    <li>Incident records maintained for education authority audit requirements</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Reporting is formatted to align with education authority internal requirements and procurement review cycles, allowing education managers to demonstrate compliance without additional administrative processing of CPC-provided documentation.
  </p>

